# Phase 3: User Interface Development and Data Model Configuration

## Overview

This phase focuses on designing the user interface and configuring the data model for the AI-Powered Job Recruitment & Candidate Management System using Salesforce. The objective is to create an intuitive application interface, configure custom tabs, establish object relationships, and organize data for efficient recruitment management.

---

## Objectives

- Create custom tabs for all objects.
- Configure page layouts.
- Build a Lightning Application.
- Establish object relationships.
- Improve user navigation and accessibility.
- Organize recruitment data efficiently.

---

## Custom Tabs

The following custom tabs are created to access the application's objects.

### Candidate Tab
Provides access to candidate information, including personal details, skills, experience, and application status.

### Job Opening Tab
Displays available job openings and allows recruiters to manage job postings.

### Recruiter Tab
Stores recruiter information and enables recruiter management.

### Interview Tab
Maintains interview schedules, interviewers, and interview results.

---

## Lightning Application

A custom Lightning App is created to provide a centralized workspace for recruiters.

### Features

- Easy navigation
- User-friendly interface
- Quick access to all recruitment modules
- Organized menu structure

---

## Page Layout Configuration

Customized page layouts are designed for each object to display important information in an organized manner.

### Candidate Layout

- Candidate Name
- Email
- Phone Number
- Skills
- Experience
- Resume
- Status

### Job Opening Layout

- Job Title
- Department
- Location
- Required Skills
- Experience Required
- Salary
- Job Status

### Interview Layout

- Candidate
- Interview Date
- Interview Time
- Interviewer
- Interview Result

---

## Object Relationships

The following relationships are configured:

- One Recruiter can manage multiple Job Openings.
- One Job Opening can receive multiple Candidate Applications.
- One Candidate can attend multiple Interviews.

These relationships help maintain data integrity and simplify record management.

---

## User Experience

The application interface is designed to provide:

- Easy navigation
- Simple data entry
- Quick record searching
- Better recruiter productivity
- Efficient recruitment tracking

---

## Expected Outcome

After completing this phase:

- All required tabs are available.
- Lightning App is configured successfully.
- Objects are connected through relationships.
- Users can easily navigate the application.
- Recruitment data is organized efficiently.

---

## Conclusion

Phase 3 successfully establishes the user interface and data model for the AI-Powered Job Recruitment & Candidate Management System. The configured tabs, layouts, and relationships improve usability and provide a structured platform for managing recruitment activities.

---

## Deliverables

- Custom Tabs
- Lightning App
- Page Layouts
- Object Relationships
- Configured Navigation
